<ul>
<li><p>Comparing row 10 and 12, we can see with the same text size of 500M, the database with shorter text and more rows (5000,10000) takes more time to build index and have a larger index size.</p>
</li>
<li><p>It looks like index building time has a meaningful correlation with text_size and index_size, which makes algorithmic sense:</p>
</li>
</ul>

