<div class="jp-Cell jp-MarkdownCell jp-Notebook-cell">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper">
<div class="jp-Collapser jp-InputCollapser jp-Cell-inputCollapser">
</div>
<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea"><div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">
</div><div class="jp-RenderedHTMLCommon jp-RenderedMarkdown jp-MarkdownOutput " data-mime-type="text/markdown">
<p>Here we observe that index_size has more linear correlation with index building time, while total text size is also a good predictor.</p>
<p>Let's guess building_time = O(text_len<sup>p</sup> · n_rows<sup>q</sup>) = index_size, we can validate this conjecture by regression:</p>
<p>log(building_time) = a + p·log(text_len) + q·log(n_rows)</p>
<p>but we only have 9 data points here, a bit short for fitting 3 free parameters, so let's make some more.</p>
<p>A new test-run is performed on text_len from 500,5000,10000,20000 and n_rows from 500 to 100000.</p>

</div>
</div>
