</div><div class="jp-RenderedHTMLCommon jp-RenderedMarkdown jp-MarkdownOutput " data-mime-type="text/markdown">
<h2 id="Conclusion">Conclusion<a class="anchor-link" href="#Conclusion">&#182;</a></h2><p>nCharIndex can accelerate substring queries by hundreds fold. The acceleration is more significant on substrings that occur less frequently in the database.</p>
<p>The smaller the result set is, the shorter time an indexed query will take. The relation between query time and query result size is highly linear with a relatively small deadweight.</p>
<p>Comparing persistence backends, metall is about 3 times faster than rocksdb.</p>
<p>Index building time is roughly O(l<sup>0.65</sup>·n<sup>1.04</sup>), where l is the average length of each text item, and n is the number of rows.</p>

</div>
