         <mrow>
           <mrow>
            <mi>b</mi>
            <mo stretchy="false">=</mo>
            <msub>
             <mi>b</mi>
             <mn>0</mn>
            </msub>
           </mrow>
           <mi>∙</mi>
           <mi>B</mi>
           <mi>∙</mi>
           <mi mathvariant="italic">SINR</mi>
           <mrow>
            <mo fence="true" form="prefix" stretchy="true">(</mo>
            <mrow>
             <mi mathvariant="italic">dB</mi>
            </mrow>
            <mo fence="true" form="postfix" stretchy="true">)</mo>
           </mrow>
          </mrow>
        </math> </span><!--Next 'div' added for floating.--><div style="display:inline; position:relative; left:-1.27cm;">.</div>.<span class="odfLiEnd"/> </div></li><li><p class="P4" style="margin-left:1.27cm;"><span class="ListLabel_20_1" style="display:block;float:left;min-width:0cm;">(3)</span>Utility as a function of net send and receive bandwidth, b<span class="T5">s</span> and b<span class="T5">r</span> of each node i(alias of channel capacity in current document) C, f<span class="T5">i</span>(C).<span class="odfLiEnd"/> </p></li></ol><p class="Standard"> </p><h1 class="Heading_20_1"><a id="a__Utility_Layer"><span/></a>Utility Layer</h1><h2 class="Heading_20_2"><a id="a__Concave_utility_function"><span/></a>Concave utility function</h2><p class="Standard">The economics definition of utility reflects node’s incentive to use certain bandwidth, or the rent a node would like to pay for a spectrum used in a certain period of time. An example is there are people who need only 0.1 channel for voice call, and people who need 3.2 channels for watching online video. Graph coloring model has omitted this utility (and thus demand) curve.</p><p class="Standard">“Concave utility function” is an assumption that can minimize computation complexity.  It has the same meaning with “marginal utility of bandwidth decreases” in economics term. The analysis will be covered later in this section.</p><h2 class="Heading_20_2"><a id="a__iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAS0AAADwCAIAAADaVqX8AAAAAXNSR0IArs4c6QAAHH9JREFUeF7tnXlgjNfex89kQYIgdk3FToXW9rpUVa2l1VZua_tLKxRtEUtvLa3tFtWESq3lCr1uLEldGulNcyvKRXItId4gEUQWiSCRyB7JbO9vZpIRkW1mzuQ5yXyfP8iZec73_M7nd77zPHOeZ54jU6vVDBsIgICkBKwkbR2NgwAIaAjAhxgHICA9AfhQ_hwgAhCoDh8uX748PT0drEEABMojYHYfBgUFrVu3bs2aNcgBCIBAeQRk5p4vdXFxiYqKsre3v3v3btOmTZEJEACB5wmY93hIB8OEhARqValU0lHR6ASoo7wdZA7eUXSJRZ2XdP7QstGy4b6xRXIl3jS6AVQEAUkJmNeHf_nLX3Jzc6mDBQUFu3btSktLq3pn87Oy5MV7y5q1_6TPjHbNZORDlb1TK4ffS_iUeFP3asmaVW8Pe4KAdATM6EP9wVDXOwMPiUm_776YqefSYsSmy14jWlDZqoGj04vOg0oSe_qm9tV